<p>

<b>Daylife, Inc</b> is an online <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../677/2351677.xml">
news aggregator</link> including a news <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../315/87315.xml">
platform</link> based on the concepts of the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../123/29123.xml">
semantic web</link><ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref>. Daylife.com is a showcase of the platform and provides access to a publicly accessible <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../ury/24th_century.xml">
API</link> <ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%222%22])">2</ref><ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%223%22])">3</ref><ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%224%22])">4</ref>. Initially known as NewsDB, Daylife is situated both as a news-browsing engine and a platform. This dual structure allows users and publishers alike a view into every subject, country, point of view, or topic in the news<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%225%22])">5</ref>.  </p>

<sec>
<st>
 Technical Specs </st>
<p>

The Daylife service provides access to  a continually growing index of all the articles and images of many thousands of sources. The sources may be established news outlets, blogs, or other. The whole platform is fully <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../354/173354.xml">
automated</link> and without human intervention. It uses various proprietary <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../775/775.xml">
algorithms</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../268/1268.xml">
AI</link>, and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../573/40573.xml">
NLP</link> to derive all its data and output.</p>

</sec>
<sec>
<st>
 Web Site Features </st>

<p>

The Daylife.com site is divided into latest news, topics, photos, covers, and my world. All aspects of the daylife site and features are searchable. Of note, is its very accurate quote extraction engine.</p>

</sec>
<sec>
<st>
 Developer API </st>
<p>

Daylife's Developer <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../ury/24th_century.xml">
API</link> <b>DayPI</b>, provides programmers with a web accessible interface to Daylifeâ€™s news aggregation and analysis service. By using the DayPI, developers can ask rich questions about the news, and retrieve data that will allow them to build applications around the answers to those questions. Both free and paid access is available.</p>

